Sri Lanka's top Tamil Tiger rebel group is in Switzerland for peace talks preparation, supported by the Swiss foreign ministry.
They advocate for negotiations to resume promptly, emphasizing a federal structure for a united Sri Lanka.
Meanwhile, internal conflicts within the rebels have led to violent clashes and killings.
The government has released some rebels on bail, aiming to revive stalled peace talks.
Japanese envoy Yasushi Akashi is working to restart negotiations between the government and rebels, with hopes for progress and reconciliation.
Peace remains elusive amidst ongoing tensions and accusations between the parties.
